cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DS

The paper discusses the behavior of excitation wave-fronts in a geometrically constrained medium, which is a topic commonly studied in the field of computational neuroscience (cs.NE). The use of the Fitzhugh-Nagumo model also suggests a focus on simulation and modeling (cs.SI). The study of how excitability controls the propagation of excitation and determines patterns of traversing a random planar graph falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The numerical analysis and exploration of patterns also suggest a focus on mathematical analysis (cs.MA) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
